<plot>Boyd Soloman believes he can fly and is eight floors above a street intending to prove it. Based on the highly acclaimed graphic novel by Brian Biggs, Dear Julia, is the story of how he got there. Boyd's vivid memory of the past and shaky comprehension of the present give him clues to the events that lead him to the edge: his childhood, his parents, and a particular trip to the country where everything began to go terribly awry.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?133705</url></doc>
